def: A genus of cruciferous plants; madwort. The sweet alyssum (A.maritimum), cultivated for bouquets, bears small, white, sweet-scented flowers.
The state of being a high-churchman. J. H. Newman.
A pain that affects only one side of the head.
One of the divisions or parties of charioteers (distinguishedby their colors) in the games of the circus.
A book kept by a depositor, in which an officer of a bankenters the debits and credits of the depositor's account with thebank.
A game at cards in which the object is to make fifteen points.
